Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/agency/Incumbency
Object: The holding of a position by a person, including the time period for which this was the case. For example, Philip Hammond holding the position of Foreign Secretary between two dates.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/agency/
Object: A model describing people and groups of people with agency. The model also describes a personâ€™s membership of and positions in groups.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/agency/hasPosition
Object: Relates an incumbency to a position. An incumbency is to a single position. A position may have one or more incumbencies, or none.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/agency/hasGroupInclusion
Object: Relates an agent to a group inclusion. An agent may have one or more group inclusions, or none. A group inclusion is to a single agent.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/agency/hasIncumbency
Object: Relates a person to an incumbency. A person may have one or more incumbencies, or none. An incumbency is to a single person.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/agency/title
Object: A person's title. For example, Mr., Ms. or Dr.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/agency/hasInterestIn
Object: Relates an agent to a concept to express an area of interest. An agent may have one or more areas of interest, or none.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/agency/GroupInclusion
Object: The inclusion of a person or group in another group over a period of time, for example: a membership of a committee or a whipping to a party.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/agency/Position
Object: A named post within a group. A position may be held by one or more people over time or at the same time, or have no holder at a particular time: for example, the post of Minister of Food, having existed in the past and having had eight successive incumbents; or a Member of the House of Commons and a Member of the House of Lords both serving as Co-Chairs of the Joint Committee on the Palace of Westminster.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/agency/placeOfBirth
Object: Relates a person to their place of birth.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/agency/Place
Object: A place named in a geography.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/agency/familyName
Object: A person's inherited name, commonly known in the west as surname.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/agency/Group
Object: A group of people. Groups may contain other groups or be empty.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/agency/positionIn
Object: Relates a position to a group. A position is in a single group. A group may have one or more positions, or none.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/agency/hasExpertiseIn
Object: Relates an agent to a concept to express an area of expertise. An agent may have one or more areas of expertise, or none.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/agency/givenName
Object: A person's personal name, commonly known in the west as first or forename.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/agency/inGroup
Object: Relates a group inclusion to a group. A group inclusion is in a single group. A group may have one or more group inclusions, or none.
